	abstract = {While it’s always possible to compute a variational approximation to a posterior distribution, it can be difﬁcult to discover problems with this approximation. We propose two diagnostic algorithms to alleviate this problem. The Paretosmoothed importance sampling (PSIS) diagnostic gives a goodness of ﬁt measurement for joint distributions, while simultaneously improving the error in the estimate. The variational simulationbased calibration (VSBC) assesses the average performance of point estimates.},
